misconceptions.inferred_category_name: No detected notional machine misconception (correct parallel swap in sort)
misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that sorting the scores array and swapping the corresponding names at the same time will keep the name-score pairing intact, and that after ascending sort the last element is the top student.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No gap here: in Java, arrays store elements by index; swapping both arrays at the same indices during the sort correctly maintains the pairing. After sorting ascending, index n-1 is indeed the maximum score.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: No error; produces correct output for the stated requirements (assuming n>0 and valid inputs).
